When You Walk In The Room

version_description: Based on the original single it is complete and in the correct key.
The chords in version one of this song the chords in both the verse and the chorus are incorrect. chord location corrected as well
There are multiple versions of this song. This tab is according to the "I'm Your Hoochie Coochie Man" version of the 1977 album "King of the Electric Blues".
Muddy plays this in the key of E with a capo on the 3rd fret, so for the authentic sound, do that, but it is very easily played without a capo.
This is a basic rhythm version and very useful to practice - barre chords, reasonably quick changes and a great 12 barre blues.
I've tried to write the chords over the word they change. In my way of thinking, if you know the song, it's not necessary to remark with a word what part of the song is. :).
Wrote out all parts of the song  easier layout for auto scroll
Chords for all instrumental and vocal parts / tab for intro picking / intermediate version with sus2, sus4 and add9 chords.
